{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1370,"text":"Imagine you're in a bar, or a club,"},{"time":7120,"text":"and you start talking, and after a while,\nthe question comes up,"},{"time":10130,"text":"\"So, what do you do for work?\""},{"time":12015,"text":"And since you think\nyour job is interesting,"},{"time":14950,"text":"you say, \"I'm a mathematician.\"\n(Laughter)"},{"time":19690,"text":"And inevitably, during that conversation"},{"time":22080,"text":"one of these two phrases come up:"},{"time":25750,"text":"A) \"I was terrible at math,\nbut it wasn't my fault."},{"time":29195,"text":"It's because the teacher\nwas awful.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":32613,"text":"Or B) \"But what is math really for?\""},{"time":35582,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":36610,"text":"I'll now address Case B."},{"time":38955,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":40510,"text":"When someone asks you what math is for,\nthey're not asking you"},{"time":45354,"text":"about applications\nof mathematical science."},{"time":48203,"text":"They're asking you,"},{"time":49554,"text":"why did I have to study that bullshit\nI never used in my life again? (Laughter)"},{"time":53485,"text":"That's what they're actually asking."},{"time":55924,"text":"So when mathematicians are asked\nwhat math is for,"},{"time":60124,"text":"they tend to fall into two groups:"},{"time":62404,"text":"54.51 percent of mathematicians\nwill assume an attacking position,"},{"time":68609,"text":"and 44.77 percent of mathematicians\nwill take a defensive position."},{"time":73559,"text":"There's a strange 0.8 percent,\namong which I include myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":77068,"text":"Who are the ones that attack?"},{"time":79155,"text":"The attacking ones are mathematicians\nwho would tell you"},{"time":81902,"text":"this question makes no sense,"},{"time":83849,"text":"because mathematics\nhave a meaning all their own --"},{"time":86597,"text":"a beautiful edifice with its own logic --"},{"time":89144,"text":"and that there's no point"},{"time":91011,"text":"in constantly searching\nfor all possible applications."},{"time":93558,"text":"What's the use of poetry?\nWhat's the use of love?"},{"time":95847,"text":"What's the use of life itself? \nWhat kind of question is that?"},{"time":98908,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":100529,"text":"Hardy, for instance, was a model\nof this type of attack."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104296,"text":"And those who stand in defense tell you,"},{"time":106242,"text":"\"Even if you don't realize it, friend,\nmath is behind everything.\""},{"time":111082,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":112340,"text":"Those guys,"},{"time":114218,"text":"they always bring up\nbridges and computers."},{"time":118246,"text":"\"If you don't know math,\nyour bridge will collapse.\""},{"time":120841,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":122286,"text":"It's true, computers are all about math."},{"time":125523,"text":"And now these guys\nhave also started saying"},{"time":128013,"text":"that behind information security\nand credit cards are prime numbers."},{"time":133710,"text":"These are the answers your math teacher\nwould give you if you asked him."},{"time":137379,"text":"He's one of the defensive ones."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139544,"text":"Okay, but who's right then?"},{"time":141384,"text":"Those who say that math\ndoesn't need to have a purpose,"},{"time":143990,"text":"or those who say that math\nis behind everything we do?"},{"time":146849,"text":"Actually, both are right."},{"time":148520,"text":"But remember I told you"},{"time":150183,"text":"I belong to that strange 0.8 percent\nclaiming something else?"},{"time":153726,"text":"So, go ahead, ask me what math is for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156929,"text":"Audience: What is math for?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":159858,"text":"Eduardo Sáenz de Cabezón: Okay,\n76.34 percent of you asked the question,"},{"time":164673,"text":"23.41 percent didn't say anything,"},{"time":167600,"text":"and the 0.8 percent --"},{"time":168827,"text":"I'm not sure what those guys are doing."},{"time":171675,"text":"Well, to my dear 76.31 percent --"},{"time":175175,"text":"it's true that math doesn't need\nto serve a purpose,"},{"time":179815,"text":"it's true that it's\na beautiful structure, a logical one,"},{"time":182685,"text":"probably one\nof the greatest collective efforts"},{"time":185537,"text":"ever achieved in human history."},{"time":187633,"text":"But it's also true that there,"},{"time":189732,"text":"where scientists and technicians\nare looking for mathematical theories"},{"time":194331,"text":"that allow them to advance,"},{"time":196641,"text":"they're within the structure of math,\nwhich permeates everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200438,"text":"It's true that we have to go\nsomewhat deeper,"},{"time":203585,"text":"to see what's behind science."},{"time":205308,"text":"Science operates on intuition, creativity."},{"time":209348,"text":"Math controls intuition\nand tames creativity."},{"time":213747,"text":"Almost everyone\nwho hasn't heard this before"},{"time":215937,"text":"is surprised when they hear\nthat if you take"},{"time":218647,"text":"a 0.1 millimeter thick sheet of paper,\nthe size we normally use,"},{"time":223187,"text":"and, if it were big enough,\nfold it 50 times,"},{"time":226505,"text":"its thickness would extend almost\nthe distance from the Earth to the sun."},{"time":232600,"text":"Your intuition tells you it's impossible."},{"time":235201,"text":"Do the math and you'll see it's right."},{"time":237622,"text":"That's what math is for."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240135,"text":"It's true that science, all types\nof science, only makes sense"},{"time":243917,"text":"because it makes us better understand\nthis beautiful world we live in."},{"time":247288,"text":"And in doing that,"},{"time":248669,"text":"it helps us avoid the pitfalls\nof this painful world we live in."},{"time":252179,"text":"There are sciences that help us\nin this way quite directly."},{"time":255657,"text":"Oncological science, for example."},{"time":257413,"text":"And there are others we look at from afar,\nwith envy sometimes,"},{"time":260904,"text":"but knowing that we are\nwhat supports them."},{"time":263464,"text":"All the basic sciences\nsupport them,"},{"time":266213,"text":"including math."},{"time":268649,"text":"All that makes science, science\nis the rigor of math."},{"time":272366,"text":"And that rigor factors in\nbecause its results are eternal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277242,"text":"You probably said or were told\nat some point"},{"time":279757,"text":"that diamonds are forever, right?"},{"time":284178,"text":"That depends on\nyour definition of forever!"},{"time":286392,"text":"A theorem -- that really is forever."},{"time":288883,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":290134,"text":"The Pythagorean theorem is still true"},{"time":293486,"text":"even though Pythagoras is dead,\nI assure you it's true. (Laughter)"},{"time":296601,"text":"Even if the world collapsed"},{"time":297946,"text":"the Pythagorean theorem\nwould still be true."},{"time":300391,"text":"Wherever any two triangle sides\nand a good hypotenuse get together"},{"time":304452,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":305673,"text":"the Pythagorean theorem goes all out.\nIt works like crazy."},{"time":308534,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":315535,"text":"Well, we mathematicians devote ourselves\nto come up with theorems."},{"time":319407,"text":"Eternal truths."},{"time":321143,"text":"But it isn't always easy to know\nthe difference between"},{"time":323909,"text":"an eternal truth, or theorem,\nand a mere conjecture."},{"time":326815,"text":"You need proof."},{"time":329829,"text":"For example,"},{"time":331596,"text":"let's say I have a big,\nenormous, infinite field."},{"time":336423,"text":"I want to cover it with equal pieces,\nwithout leaving any gaps."},{"time":340132,"text":"I could use squares, right?"},{"time":342256,"text":"I could use triangles.\nNot circles, those leave little gaps."},{"time":346777,"text":"Which is the best shape to use?"},{"time":349134,"text":"One that covers the same surface,\nbut has a smaller border."},{"time":353687,"text":"In the year 300, Pappus of Alexandria\nsaid the best is to use hexagons,"},{"time":358396,"text":"just like bees do."},{"time":360243,"text":"But he didn't prove it."},{"time":361990,"text":"The guy said, \"Hexagons, great!\nLet's go with hexagons!\""},{"time":364688,"text":"He didn't prove it,\nit remained a conjecture."},{"time":367656,"text":"\"Hexagons!\""},{"time":369334,"text":"And the world, as you know,\nsplit into Pappists and anti-Pappists,"},{"time":372964,"text":"until 1700 years later"},{"time":378253,"text":"when in 1999, Thomas Hales proved"},{"time":383707,"text":"that Pappus and the bees were right --\nthe best shape to use was the hexagon."},{"time":388641,"text":"And that became a theorem,\nthe honeycomb theorem,"},{"time":391123,"text":"that will be true forever and ever,"},{"time":393183,"text":"for longer than any diamond\nyou may have. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":396229,"text":"But what happens if we go\nto three dimensions?"},{"time":399033,"text":"If I want to fill the space\nwith equal pieces,"},{"time":403464,"text":"without leaving any gaps,"},{"time":404805,"text":"I can use cubes, right?"},{"time":406638,"text":"Not spheres, those leave little gaps.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":409994,"text":"What is the best shape to use?"},{"time":412957,"text":"Lord Kelvin, of the famous\nKelvin degrees and all,"},{"time":417607,"text":"said that the best was to use\na truncated octahedron"},{"time":424791,"text":"which, as you all know --"},{"time":427507,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":429035,"text":"is this thing here!"},{"time":430814,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":435778,"text":"Come on."},{"time":438025,"text":"Who doesn't have a truncated\noctahedron at home? (Laughter)"},{"time":440862,"text":"Even a plastic one."},{"time":442089,"text":"\"Honey, get the truncated octahedron,\nwe're having guests.\""},{"time":444846,"text":"Everybody has one!\n(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":446240,"text":"But Kelvin didn't prove it."},{"time":448614,"text":"It remained a conjecture --\nKelvin's conjecture."},{"time":452655,"text":"The world, as you know, then split into\nKelvinists and anti-Kelvinists"},{"time":458177,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":459599,"text":"until a hundred or so years later,"},{"time":466203,"text":"someone found a better structure."},{"time":470917,"text":"Weaire and Phelan\nfound this little thing over here --"},{"time":476026,"text":"(Laughter) --"},{"time":477665,"text":"this structure to which they gave\nthe very clever name"},{"time":481209,"text":"\"the Weaire-Phelan structure.\""},{"time":483375,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":485911,"text":"It looks like a strange object,\nbut it isn't so strange,"},{"time":488568,"text":"it also exists in nature."},{"time":490239,"text":"It's very interesting that this structure,"},{"time":492844,"text":"because of its geometric properties,"},{"time":495037,"text":"was used to build the Aquatics Center\nfor the Beijing Olympic Games."}]},{"cues":[{"time":500969,"text":"There, Michael Phelps\nwon eight gold medals,"},{"time":503714,"text":"and became the best swimmer of all time."},{"time":506875,"text":"Well, until someone better\ncomes along, right?"},{"time":510616,"text":"As may happen\nwith the Weaire-Phelan structure."},{"time":513015,"text":"It's the best\nuntil something better shows up."},{"time":515633,"text":"But be careful, because this one\nreally stands a chance"},{"time":520225,"text":"that in a hundred or so years,\nor even if it's in 1700 years,"},{"time":525205,"text":"that someone proves\nit's the best possible shape for the job."},{"time":530978,"text":"It will then become a theorem,\na truth, forever and ever."},{"time":535348,"text":"For longer than any diamond."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538837,"text":"So, if you want to tell someone"},{"time":543777,"text":"that you will love them forever"},{"time":546823,"text":"you can give them a diamond."},{"time":548890,"text":"But if you want to tell them\nthat you'll love them forever and ever,"},{"time":552421,"text":"give them a theorem!"},{"time":554172,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":555263,"text":"But hang on a minute!"},{"time":558783,"text":"You'll have to prove it,"},{"time":560183,"text":"so your love doesn't remain"},{"time":562466,"text":"a conjecture."}]},{"cues":[{"time":564299,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}